properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued February 2 at 10:22AM MST until February 3 at 9:00PM MST by NWS Albuquerque NM
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds 35 to 45 mph with gusts up to 65 mph
possible.

* WHERE...West Central Plateau, West Central Mountains,
Southwest Mountains, South Central Highlands, Upper Tularosa
Valley, South Central Mountains, Eastern Lincoln County,
Southwest Chaves County and San Agustin Plains and Adjacent
Lowlands.

* WHEN...From Monday morning through Monday evening.

* IMPACTS...High winds may move loose debris, damage property
and cause power outages. Travel could be difficult especially
for high profile vehicles. This includes portions of
Interstate 40 and U.S. Highway 60 from the Continental Divide
to the Arizona border.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strong winds may combine with snow from
Gallup down to the Gila through McKinley, Cibola, and Catron
Counties. This will create lower visibility for those
traveling in these areas Monday afternoon.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM MONDAY MORNING THROUGH MONDAY EVENING
